</div><div class="columnMacro conf-macro output-block" data-hasbody="true" data-macro-name="column"><h1 id="HiringGuideHomeandInstructions-WelcometoRyerson'sHiringGuide!">Welcome to Ryerson's Hiring Guide!</h1><p>This Hiring Guide has been developed by Human Resources to help hiring committees and managers find the best faculty, instructors, and staff to further the mission and goals of the University. We encourage everyone to provide constructive comments that will help us to build continuous improvements into the hiring guide, to share hiring experiences with our colleagues, and to solicit ideas, feedback, and help on what works best in the university environment, for example, links to websites, relevant data, or useful information. </p><h5 id="HiringGuideHomeandInstructions-Jointheconversation">Join the conversation</h5><p>To join the conversation, please log in with your my.ryerson ID by clicking on 'Log In' on the top right beside the search bar. Then click on the 'Add Comment' link at the bottom of the page. If you would like to receive an email notification when there is a reply to your comment, please click on the 'Tools' menu (top right) and choose 'Watch'. If you would like to receive an email when there are changes to any/all pages in the hiring guide, please click on 'Browse', 'Advanced', and 'Start watching this space' under 'Subscribe'.</p><p>The hiring guide is a space for collegiality and collaboration so we will remove comments that do not contribute to this goal.  Please be sure you adhere to Ryerson's policies and guidelines such as civility, discrimination and harassment prevention, confidentiality, and privacy.  In particular, be sure to never include details that might identify an individual, for example a candidate or hiring panel member.</p><p>Click on the <a href="/display/RHR/Introduction">Introduction</a> to start.</p></div></div></div></div>

                
        
    
